com.usc.bill.dto

Class Bill

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.usc.bill.dto.Bill

  • public class Bill
extends java.lang.Object
    A Bill is a a complex structure computed at the end of a term for a student. It contains attributes about the student to which the bill applies, such as demographics, the list of courses taken by the student, and the list of transactions (charges and payments), comprising the bill.
    Version:
    1.0 11/19/2017
    Author:
    WU, Alamri, STROUD

    • Field Detail

      • addressCity

        private java.lang.String addressCity
        The city portion of the address, e.g. "New York City", "Columbia", "Atlanta", etc. of the student to which the bill is associated.

      • addressPostalCode

        private java.lang.String addressPostalCode
        The ZIP code, aka Postal Code, portion of the address, e.g. 29170, 10026, etc., of the student to which the bill is associated.

      • addressState

        private java.lang.String addressState
        The state, e.g. SC, GA, NY, etc., of the student to which the bill is associated.

      • addressStreet

        private java.lang.String addressStreet
        The street address of the student to which the bill is associated.

      • classStatus

        private java.lang.String classStatus
        The name of the year or class of the student, e.g. Freshman, Sophomore, Junior, etc., to which the bill is associated to. ClassStatus will be translated to the enumerated type ClassStatus and its value restricted as such.

      • college

        private java.lang.String college
        The school being attended by the student to which the bill is associated. College will be translated to the enum type College and its value restricted by this type.

      • courses

        private java.util.List<Course> courses
        The list of courses taken by the student to which the bill is associated. Each item in the list is a complex object, Course, containing the attributes of this class, such as a cource name and number of credit hours.

      • emailAddress

        private java.lang.String emailAddress
        The email address of the student to which the bill is associated.

      • firstName

        private java.lang.String firstName
        The first name of the student to which the bill is associated. E.g. if the student is "John Doe" the first name is "John".

      • id

        private java.lang.String id
        The unique id of the bill, generated by the system and used as the identifier of the bill.

      • lastName

        private java.lang.String lastName
        The last name of the student to which the bill is associated. E.g. if the student is "John doe" the last name is "Doe".

      • phone

        private java.lang.String phone
        The phone number of the student to which the bill is associated.

      • transactions

        private java.util.List<Transaction> transactions
        The list of transactions, i.e. payments and charges, made or incurred by the student for which the bill is associated. Each item in the list is a complex object, Transaction, containing attributes of this class, such as a dollar amount and a type, for payment or charge.
